# FlyRank Frontend AI Engineering - GitHub Copilot Custom Instructions

## 1. Environment & Stack
- Framework: Next.js 15 (App Router, React 19)
- Language: TypeScript (Strict Mode enabled)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Form Management: `react-hook-form` + `zod`

## 2. Form & Data Validation Rules (Enforced via FE-03)
- RULE_FORM_01: Uncontrolled form inputs are strictly prohibited. All forms MUST use `react-hook-form` bound with a `zod` schema resolver.
- RULE_FORM_02: Never handle manual loading states with arbitrary `useState` flags when using forms. Always utilize `formState.isSubmitting` provided by `react-hook-form`.
- RULE_FORM_03: Every interactive form element MUST supply explicit `aria-invalid`, `aria-describedby`, and `htmlFor` bindings for WCAG accessibility compliance.

## 3. Engineering Quality Constraints
- Always prefer modular component splitting over monolithic files (>150 lines should be refactored into sub-components).
- Do NOT use explicit `any` types under any circumstances. Define strict interfaces or leverage Zod dynamic types (`z.infer`).
- All automated commit suggestions MUST follow Conventional Commits 1.0.0 (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`).